 A public office is a position provided for by the Constitution and other normative legal acts, or a position established in accordance with the procedure established by the legislation of the Kyrgyz Republic (hereinafter referred to as the legislation) as a staff unit of a state body with a defined range of duties for the person holding it to fulfill and ensure the powers of this body. Government positions are divided into political, special and administrative ones.;
